Wash and dry all produce. Halve, deseed, and dice @long green pepper{1}(halved, deseeded, and diced into ½-inch pieces). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens. Mince @garlic{2%cloves}(minced).

Poke @sweet potatoes{2} on all sides with a fork. Place on a large #microwave-safe plate{}. Microwave until tender, carefully flipping with #tongs halfway through, ~{6-10%minutes}.

> If potatoes are still firm, continue to microwave in 1-minute intervals until easily pierced with a fork.

Remove from microwave and let cool slightly.

Meanwhile, heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a medium #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add green pepper, scallion whites, and garlic. Cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add @ground beef{10%ounce}, @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add @tomato paste{1.5%ounce} to pot and cook until fragrant, about ~{1%minute}. Add @beef stock concentrate{1} and @water{1/2%cup}. Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly thickened, ~{5-8%minutes}.

> Use 3/4 cup water for 4 servings.

Halve sweet potatoes lengthwise; fluff insides with a fork. Spread with @butter{1%tablespoon} and season with @salt{to taste}.

> Use 2 TBSP butter for 4 servings.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} (use as much as you like), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Add @water{1%tsp} at a time, until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Divide finished sweet potatoes between plates. Top with chili. Sprinkle with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup} and scallion greens. Drizzle with hot sauce crema.